      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some stuff about the heat death of the universe... it's hard to wrap my head around the fact that every single thing we do, every struggle, every bit of pain, is just going to be erased by absolute zero entropy eventually. it makes everything feel so incredibly pointless. like, why even bother trying to exist if the math says it all ends in nothing anyway?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
