      "content": "but that feels like such a hollow comfort. \"it matters\" to who? to a bunch of atoms that are just gonna be scattered anyway? it feels like people just say that because they're too scared to admit that the nothingness is the only thing that’s actually certain. if everything is just a temporary glitch in a system that's heading toward zero, isn't the only logical way to deal with the suffering to just... stop participating? like, isn't it more rational to embrace the void than to fight a war you've already lost?",
