      "content": "it's just the sheer weight of the futility. like, every single emotion and every single person is just a brief flicker of noise before the silence. if the end result is exactly the same no matter what i do, then the \"struggle\" is just unnecessary friction. why keep the engine running if it's only producing heat that's eventually going to dissipate into nothing? it feels like we're all just being cruel to ourselves by insisting on continuing something that has no point.",
